==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nebuly
<hw>Neb"u*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>n⟦eacute⟧bul⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Composed
of successive short curves supposed to resemble a cloud; -- said of a
heraldic line by which an ordinary or subordinary may be
bounded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nebulization</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nebuly
<hw>Neb"u*ly</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Her. & Arch.)</fld> <def>A line
or a decoration composed of successive short curves or waves supposed to
resemble a cloud. See <er>N⟦eacute⟧bul⟦eacute⟧</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necessarian</ent>⟦br⟧
